main event: An unidentified large object with a vapor trail was observed traveling at high speed from the north to southwest in Melbourne, Australia in May 1952.
interesting points: The object was seen traveling at a very high speed and estimated altitude of about 50,000 ft.,The object left a vapor trail behind it as it flew across the sky.,There were multiple sightings reported around the same time in Melbourne.,Witnesses described the object as being cigar-shaped and brighter than a typical shooting star.,The sighting lasted between 10 to 13 seconds.
witness description: a Southern Command Intelligence Officer and various other witnesses including a taxi driver and airline pilot
